Setup

If specific pathways are more likely to be predicted we can get a relative closeness value where each pathway score is normalised to itself

graper <- read_csv(here::here("Project_Datasets", "Pathway_analysis_cluster", "graper.csv"), 
    col_names = F) %>% setNames(c("Drug", "Correlation", "Pvalue", "Pathway"))
graper <- graper %>% filter(between(Pvalue, 0, 1)) %>% group_by(Pathway) %>% mutate(P_value_adjust = p.adjust(Pvalue, 
    method = "fdr"))

Best_prediction <- graper %>% group_by(Drug) %>% summarise(max_corr = max(Correlation)) %>% 
    na.omit()

hist(Best_prediction$max_corr)

Unpredicted_Drugs <- Best_prediction %>% filter(max_corr < 0.2) %>% pull(Drug)

Grouped_original_pathway <- graper %>% filter(!(Drug %in% Unpredicted_Drugs)) %>% 
    inner_join(drug_targets[, 1:2], by = "Drug") %>% group_by(Pathway, Reactome_Pathway) %>% 
    add_tally(name = "Drugs_per_pathway") %>% ungroup %>% # filter(P_value_adjust<0.05) %>% add_tally(name =
# 'Significant_Drugs_per_pathway')%>%
filter(Drugs_per_pathway > 3) %>% group_split(Pathway) %>% setNames(., map_chr(., 
    ~(unique(.x[["Pathway"]]))))
Grouped_response_pathway <- graper %>% filter(!(Drug %in% Unpredicted_Drugs)) %>% 
    inner_join(drug_targets[, 1:2], by = "Drug") %>% group_by(Pathway, Reactome_Pathway) %>% 
    add_tally(name = "Drugs_per_pathway") %>% ungroup %>% # filter(P_value_adjust<0.05) %>% add_tally(name =
# 'Significant_Drugs_per_pathway')%>%
filter(Drugs_per_pathway > 3) %>% group_split(Reactome_Pathway) %>% setNames(., map_chr(., 
    ~(unique(.x[["Reactome_Pathway"]]))))

Drug_prediction_plot <- function(x, include_legend = F) {
    # include_legend = F
    if (include_legend == T) {
        legending = NULL
    } else {
        legending = theme(legend.position = "none")
    }
    # x = graper2[[1]] %>% as.data.frame()
    high_Pathways <- x %>% group_by(Reactome_Pathway) %>% summarise(mean_drug = mean(Correlation)) %>% 
        filter(mean_drug > 0.3) %>% pull(Reactome_Pathway)
    # Pathway_of_interest = 'Activation of BAD and translocation to mitochondria'
    test <- x %>% filter(Reactome_Pathway %in% high_Pathways)
    if (nrow(test) < 2) {
        unique(x$Pathway)
    } else {
        test %>% # mutate(of_interest = if_else(Reactome_Pathway == Pathway_of_interest, 'blue',
        # 'grey80')) %>%
        ggplot(aes(x = Correlation, fill = Reactome_Pathway, colour = Reactome_Pathway)) + 
            # geom_histogram(alpha=0.6, position = 'identity') +theme_bw()
        # #+theme(legend.position = 'none')
        geom_density(alpha = 0.05) + theme_bw() + ggtitle(paste("Predictions by:", 
            unique(x$Pathway))) + legending
    }
}

Pathway_prediction_plot <- function(x) {
    # x = Grouped_response_pathway[[1]]
    
    high_Pathways <- x %>% group_by(Pathway) %>% summarise(mean_drug = mean(Correlation)) %>% 
        filter(mean_drug > 0.25) %>% pull(Pathway)
    test <- x %>% filter(Pathway %in% high_Pathways)
    if (nrow(test) < 2) {
        unique(x$Reactome_Pathway)
    } else {
        test %>% # mutate(of_interest = if_else(Reactome_Pathway == Pathway_of_interest, 'blue',
        # 'grey80')) %>%
        ggplot(aes(x = Correlation, fill = Pathway, colour = Pathway)) + # geom_histogram(alpha=0.6, position = 'identity') +theme_bw()
        # #+theme(legend.position = 'none')
        geom_density(alpha = 0.05) + theme_bw() + ggtitle(paste("Predictions for:", 
            unique(x$Reactome_Pathway))) + theme(legend.position = "none")
    }
}
